Privacy Policy

App: Cycelle (Period Tracker, Pregnancy, AI)
Developer: AppNestMath
Package name: app.reglapp.app
Last updated: June 5, 2025

This Privacy Policy explains how your personal data is collected, used, stored, and protected when you use the Cycelle mobile application (the "App"). By using the App, you agree to this policy.

1. Data Controller

The data controller is AppNestMath. For privacy-related questions, you can contact us at:

Email: support@reglapp.com
2. Data We Collect

The App may collect and process the following types of data:

2.1 Account Information

Email address
Name / display name (optional)
Authentication credentials (via Firebase Authentication)
Basic profile information from your Google account when you sign in with Google
2.2 Health and Cycle Data

Menstrual cycle dates and durations
Daily logs (symptoms, flow intensity, notes, etc.)
Mood logs
Pregnancy tracking data (when used)
Reminder and notification preferences
2.3 Artificial Intelligence (AI) Chat Data

Messages you send to the AI assistant
AI responses
Cycle and health context data used to generate responses
2.4 Technical and Usage Data

Device type and operating system version
App version
Crash and error logs
Advertising ID (via Google AdMob)
Push notification token (Firebase Cloud Messaging)
2.5 Locally Stored Data

App preferences and settings (SharedPreferences / Hive)
Private mode preference
3. How We Use Your Data

Collected data is used for the following purposes:

Creating accounts, signing in, and authentication
Providing menstrual cycle, pregnancy, and health tracking features
Sending personalized reminders and notifications
Providing health and cycle information through the AI assistant
Displaying statistics and trend analysis
Improving app performance and fixing errors
Displaying ads (Google AdMob)
Complying with legal obligations
4. Data Sharing

We do not sell your personal data. Your data may be shared only with the following service providers, to the extent necessary for the App to function:

Google Firebase – authentication, database (Firestore), file storage, push notifications
Google Gemini AI – generating AI chat responses (message and context data)
Google AdMob – displaying ads
Google Sign-In – signing in with a Google account
These service providers are subject to their own privacy policies:

Google Privacy Policy: https://policies.google.com/privacy
Firebase Privacy: https://firebase.google.com/support/privacy
5. Data Retention and Security

Your data is stored on secure servers in the Google Firebase infrastructure.
Data is encrypted in transit (HTTPS/TLS).
When you delete your account, associated data is deleted or anonymized within a reasonable time.
When Private Mode is enabled, certain data is not sent to cloud servers.
6. Your Rights

Under applicable privacy laws (including KVKK and GDPR), you have the right to:

Request access to your data
Request correction of your data
Request deletion of your data
Object to data processing
Request data portability
To exercise these rights, email us at support@reglapp.com.

7. Account and Data Deletion

To delete your account and data:

You may use the in-app account deletion option (if available), or
Send an account deletion request to support@reglapp.com.
Your request will be processed within 30 days at the latest.

8. Children's Privacy

The App is not intended for children under 13. We do not knowingly collect personal data from anyone under 13. If we become aware of such a case, the related data will be deleted promptly.

9. Advertising

The App may display Google AdMob ads. AdMob may collect device identifiers and usage data for ad personalization. You can manage your ad preferences in your device settings.

10. Notifications

We may request notification permission on your device to send reminder and informational notifications. You can turn this off at any time in your device settings.

11. Changes to This Policy

We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. Significant changes will be announced in the App or on this page. Continued use of the App after an update means you accept the revised policy.
Third-Party AI Processing

To provide personalized responses in the in-app AI assistant and to generate
health analyses, we send certain data you enter in the app to Google's Gemini
AI service (Google LLC / Google Ireland Ltd.).

The data sent may include: your menstrual cycle records, symptoms, mood entries,
and personal notes. This data is transmitted only when you use an AI feature
(the AI chat assistant or an AI analysis), and only after you have given your
explicit in-app consent.

- We do not send your name, email address, or account identifiers to the AI service.
- The data is used solely to generate a response or analysis for you.
- Google processes this data under its own privacy terms, which provide
  protections equivalent to those described in this policy. See Google's Privacy
  Policy at https://policies.google.com/privacy and the Gemini API terms at
  https://ai.google.dev/gemini-api/terms.
- You can withdraw your consent at any time in Settings → Artificial
  Intelligence → AI Data Sharing. When consent is off, no data is sent to the
  AI service.
